Dionne Hoskins-Brown

Bio

Dr. Hoskin’s-Brown interests are ecology of marine sediments, invertebrate fisheries, Gullah Geechee communities, diversity in science

Education

University of South Carolina | South Carolina

Ph D. Marine Science | 1999

Savannah State College | Georgia

B.S. Marine Science | 1992

Experience

Director, NOAA Sponsored Programs | Savannah State University | 2008 - Present

Commissioner |Gullah-Geechee Cultural Heritage Corridor Commission (DoI/NPS) | 2017-2022 chair; 2019 - president

Commissioner and Chair | Chatham County Resource Protection Commission | 2008 - 2016

Associate Graduate Professor | Marine Science Program, Savannah State University |April 2002 - present

**Assistant Research Professor* | Marine Science Program, Savannah State University | August 1999 - April 2002

**Postdoctoral Research Associate,r* | Center for Marine, Environmental Science and Biotechnology Research, Savannah State University | August 1999 - January 2000

**Cooperative Education Student* | DOC/NOAA/National Ocean Service, Ecotoxicology Division, Charleston, SC | April 1999 - December 1999
